{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
{{COinS safe|n}}
<!-- Please place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata (see [[</nowiki>[[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]<nowiki>]]) -->

==Usage==
This template is used to mark an [[International Standard Serial Number]] (ISSN) that may not be valid. For example:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
{{issn|1234-56789}} {{Please check ISSN}}
</syntaxhighlight>

The template does not produce any visible change to the article (unless the article is viewed in preview mode):

{{issn|1234-56789}} {{Please check ISSN|1234-56789}}

Rather, it adds the article to the hidden maintenance/tracking category: [[:Category:Articles with invalid ISSNs]].

In preview mode, it shows the warning message <span class="error" style="font-size:100%; font-weight:normal">(Warning: Check ISSN)</span>.  This warning is shown only in preview mode.

==Parameters==
The optional parameter {{para|reason}} simply provides a comment to explain why the ISSN may not be valid. For example:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
{{issn|1234-56789}} {{Please check ISSN|reason=Too many digits.}}
</syntaxhighlight>

==See also==
*{{Tl|ISSN-needed}}
*{{Tl|Listed Invalid ISSN}}

